&lt;p&gt;With first place of employment/study:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Joining the group</title><link>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/joining-the-group/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/joining-the-group/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thank you for you interest in joining the group!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unfortunately, due to large volumes of email, I am not able to respond to individual inquiries about joining Princeton or our group. Some general details can be found below.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap"&gt;
 &lt;h3 id="high-school-and-undergraduate-students"
 &gt;
 High school and undergraduate students
 &lt;/h3&gt;
 &lt;a data-clipboard-text="https://mbraverm.github.io/team/joining-the-group/#high-school-and-undergraduate-students" class="gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center" title="Anchor to: High school and undergraduate students" aria-label="Anchor to: High school and undergraduate students" href="#high-school-and-undergraduate-students"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="gdoc-icon gdoc_link"&gt;&lt;use xlink:href="#gdoc_link"&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Princeton undergrad, and are interested in the possibility of doing Junior/Senior independent work, please email me to make an appointment and discuss your interests. You can browse this page and look at the &lt;a
 class="gdoc-markdown__link"
 href="https://mbraverm.github.io/research/all-papers/"
&gt;papers&lt;/a&gt; to get an idea of the topics we&amp;rsquo;re working on. Please also look at potential IW topics &lt;a
 class="gdoc-markdown__link"
 href="https://www.cs.princeton.edu/ugrad/independent-work/undergraduate-research-topics"
&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Postdoc opportunities</title><link>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/postdoc-opportunities/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/postdoc-opportunities/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have several exciting postdoctoral opportunities in Princeton and the area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap"&gt;
 &lt;h3 id="princeton-cs-theory-group"
 &gt;
 Princeton CS Theory group:
 &lt;/h3&gt;
 &lt;a data-clipboard-text="https://mbraverm.github.io/team/postdoc-opportunities/#princeton-cs-theory-group" class="gdoc-page__anchor clip flex align-center" title="Anchor to: Princeton CS Theory group:" aria-label="Anchor to: Princeton CS Theory group:" href="#princeton-cs-theory-group"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="gdoc-icon gdoc_link"&gt;&lt;use xlink:href="#gdoc_link"&gt;&lt;/use&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please see Princeton academic jobs portal &lt;a
 class="gdoc-markdown__link"
 href="https://dof.princeton.edu/academicjobs"
&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, and navigate to opportunities in Computer Science.
The Theory Group typically advertises a postdoctoral research associate position and an associate research scholar position, which is slightly more senior. Both positions
are reviewed in the late Fall, with the goal of making decisions by January/February.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Undergraduate projects</title><link>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/undergraduate-projects/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mbraverm.github.io/team/undergraduate-projects/</guid><description>&lt;div class="flex align-center gdoc-page__anchorwrap"&gt;
